page.title: 16Wild Flowers in Woodhalls
page.content: There is luxuriant growth in the hedgerows.Here are some of the wild flowers and plants to be found:- Foxglove,hogweed,wild strawberry,dock cranesbill,vetch,ferns knapweed, common spotted orchid,clover,scabious yellow flag,dog-rose,sedges,rosebay willow herb,thistles,primrose,violet, toadflax, meadowsweet, pennywort,Welsh poppy,dandelion,daisy,celandine,herb robert,bluebell,honeysuckle,daffodil, bracken,brambles,cuckoo-pint,red campion,stitchwort,buttercup,tufted vetch,fools parsley,hard head, ragwort Because the hedges are trimmed back many of these flowers bloom a second time;for example:red campion which comes into flower in April can also be found blossoming in October. There is only a short time,in the hardest part of the winter when no wild flowers are to be found.
